ell as 14 Congenital Heart Defects: tetralogy of Fallot (TOF), Transposition of the Great Arteries (dTGA, lTGA),  hypoplastic left heart syndrome (HLHS MS-AA, HLHS MAAA), Critical Aortic Stenosis (CritAS), Atrio-Ventricular Septal Defect (AVSD, uAVSD) Double Outlet Right Ventricle (DORV) and more.", "short_description": "Fetal Heart VR is a self-teaching tool to learn geometry, anatomy, and function of Congenital Heart Diseases.\nWith the app, you can make a virtual ultrasound scan of normal and abnormal heart models and learn specific anatomical features typical for Congenital Heart Diseases. The controller simulates the ultrasound probe - by moving it like an ultrasound probe you can obtain all recommended fetal cardiac views for prenatal examination."}]}, "developer_name": "MWU Software", "developer_privacy_policy_url": "https://mwu.gridproducts.pl/privacy-policy/", "developer_terms_of_service_url": "https://mwu.gridproducts.pl/terms-and-conditions/", "publisher_name": "MWU 3D Models z.o.o.", "support_website_url": "http://mwusoftware.com/", "website_url": "https://mwu.gridproducts.pl/", "category": "APPS", "comfort_rating": "NOT_RATED", "comfort_tags": [], "context_category": {"id": "362692211442873", "context_category": "APPS"}, "context_topics": [{"id": "514087707868786"}, {"id": "478089301798119"}, {"id": "1043107547362485"}], "external_subscription_type": "NOT_REQUIRED", "genres": ["MEDICINE", "SIMULATION", "EDUCATIONAL"], "has_in_app_ads": null, "internet_connection": "NOT_REQUIRED", "play_area": "MOVEMENT", "recommended_graphics": null, "recommended_memory_gb": null, "recommended_processor": null, "supported_in_app_languages": ["en"], "supported_input_devices": ["OCULUS_TOUCH"], "supported_player_modes": ["SITTING", "STANDING", "ROOM_SCALE"], "supported_tracking_modes": [], "user_interaction_modes": ["SINGLE_USER"], "id": "979002403045325"}}]}, "scheduled_offers": {"count": 0, "nodes": []}, "baseline_offer": null, "is_approved": true, "firstOffer": {"nodes": []}, "liveChannel": {"nodes": [{"latest_supported_binary": {"__typename": "AndroidBinary", "binary_test_results": {"nodes": []}, "id": "3822305317879282", "version": "2.04"}, "id": "802061334078040", "channel_name": "LIVE"}]}, "is_for_oculus_keys_only": false, "primary_binaries": {"nodes": [{"__typename": "AndroidBinary", "__isAppBinary": "AndroidBinary", "binary_application": {"__typename": "Application", "id": "3672461322863683", "is_concept": false, "latest_released_binary": {"__typename": "AndroidBinary", "id": "3822305317879282"}, "release_status": "RELEASED"}, "binary_release_channels": {"nodes": [{"channel_name": "LIVE", "id": "802061334078040"}]}, "change_log": "Fetal Heart VR version:2.0.4. \n------ \n\nThis is an initial release of our Fetal Heart VR app prepared for Oculus Quest and Quest 2, and a major upgrade from the Oculus Go version. \n\nWHAT'S NEW: \n- In the Quest version you are able to completely reproduce all the movements done with the echo probe during the examination, \n- The design of the Quest platform allowed us to improve the interface significantly. \n- This version covers a completely new model of the Normal Heart, that includes much more anatomical detail of the Heart and nearby cardiovascular structures. \n- In this version, we start to introduce Quizzes - a way to challenge yourself with recognizing different Congenital Heart Defects. \n- Freeze and CINE options are now available \n- for Normal Heart, recommended views from ISUOG, AIUM, and ASE guidelines can be detected \n- you can turn on the natural movements of the fetus that occur during any echo examination. \n\nSUPPORT & QUESTIONS\nAre you having problems? Do you have a suggestion for a new feature? Please, write to us: \ninfo@mwusoftware.com \n\nHave a great day! \nPiotr from MWU Software", "created_date": 1623096733, "id": "3822305317879282", "version": "2.04", "version_code": 15, "release_status": "RELEASED", "status": "APPROVED", "binary_test_results": {"nodes": []}, "o